7 AS INTRODUCED
8 A Joint Resolution approving certain proposed
permanent rules of certain energy and agricultural
9 state agencies; and directing distribution.
10
11
12 WHEREAS, pursuant to Section 308 of Title 75 of the Oklahoma
13 Statutes, the Oklahoma State Legislature shall adopt a joint
14 resolution to approve or disapprove administrative rules.
15 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
16 AND THE SENATE OF THE 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
17 SECTION 1. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
18 permanent rules of the Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and
19 Forestry filed on or before February 1, 2026.
20 SECTION 2. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
21 permanent rules of the Capitol-Medical Center Improvement and Zoning
22 Commission filed on or before February 1, 2026.
23
24
Req. No. 17318 Page 1

1 SECTION 3. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
2 permanent rules of the Corporation Commission filed on or before
3 February 1, 2026.
4 SECTION 4. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
5 permanent rules of the Department of Environmental Quality filed on
6 or before February 1, 2026.
7 SECTION 5. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
8 permanent rules of the Oklahoma Liquified Petroleum Gas Board filed
9 on or before February 1, 2026.
10 SECTION 6. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
11 permanent rules of the Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation Department
12 filed on or before February 1, 2026.
13 SECTION 7. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
14 permanent rules of the Oklahoma Water Resources Board filed on or
15 before February 1, 2026.
16 SECTION 8. The Legislature hereby approves all proposed
17 permanent rules of the Department of Wildlife Conservation filed on
18 or before February 1, 2026.
19 SECTION 9. The Oklahoma Secretary of State is hereby directed
20 to distribute copies of this resolution to the Governor and the
21 editor of "The Oklahoma Register".
